ice"},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"If the error can be fixed by the customer within the Apple Pay sheet, we return an NSError that can be displayed in the Apple Pay sheet.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Otherwise, the original error is returned, resulting in the Apple Pay sheet being dismissed. You should display the error message to the customer afterwards.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Currently, we convert billing address related errors into a PKPaymentError that helpfully points to the billing address field in the Apple Pay sheet."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Note that Apple Pay should prevent most card errors (e.g. invalid CVC, expired cards) when you add a card to the wallet.","type":"text"}]}}}